      "amount": "2 tbsp"
    },
    {
      "name": "Water or chicken broth",
      "amount": "1/2 cup"
    },
    {
      "name": "Fresh parsley",
      "amount": "1 handful"
    },
    {
      "name": "Pepper flakes",
      "amount": "to taste"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Clean and season the fish fillets with salt and pepper.",
    "Finely chop garlic, onions, and tomatoes. Sauté the onions in oil until translucent.",
    "Add chopped garlic to the sautéed onions and cook for a minute or two. Add soy sauce and white wine (if using).",
    "Simmer gently until the liquid reduces by half. Stir in water or broth, adjust seasoning with pepper flakes.",
    "Gently poach fish fillets in this sauce for about 5 minutes per side or until cooked through. Garnish with fresh parsley before serving."
  ],
